     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="9"/>
   <head>On Vsurers.</head>
   <l>OF all men vs'rers are not least accurst;</l>
   <l>They robbe the Spittle, pinch th' afflicted worst:</l>
   <l>In others griefe they'r most delighted in;</l>
   <l>Whilst Giuers suffer for the Takers sinne:</l>
   <l>O how vniust a trade of life is that,</l>
   <l>Which makes the lab'rers, leane, and th' idle, fatte?</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>FRA. QVARLES.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
